=Bio=

[[File:Kelly small.png|180px|thumb|left]]

Kelly (Kalliopi) Pavlaki is a fellow of the P2P Lab research collective. She is the project and communication manager of the COSMOLOCALISM research project funded by the ERC Starting Grant at Tallinn University of Technology. Kelly holds a BSc in Civil Infrastructures Engineering (2011-Alexander Technological Educational Institute of Thessaloniki) and an MSc in Energy Systems (2014 – International Hellenic University). She has a five-year experience in the private sector, working as part of a team on energy inspections and as a consultant of private and public organizations on the management of co-financed projects.






